[Episode 1]

4
00:01:53,090 --> 00:01:57,380
[2002, Xuecheng]

5
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:33,800
Awesome, Captain Peng.

6
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:34,650
Great, Captain Peng!

7
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:35,520
Captain Peng, you're amazing!

8
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:42,710
Admit defeat?

9
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:44,329
Nope.

10
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,000
Now the red team is challenging the blue team to a duel.

11
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:49,400
Go for it! C'mon!

12
00:03:04,090 --> 00:03:05,060
Nice!

13
00:03:06,030 --> 00:03:06,750
The blue team wins!

14
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:10,460
Captain Peng is indeed mightier.

15
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:15,190
I don't even want to call you out.

16
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:17,000
The high-sticking,

17
00:03:17,329 --> 00:03:20,000
and kneeing the others.

18
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,400
Are you proud of this sort of victory?

19
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,280
Seriously?

20
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,840
Your team was busy playing tricks too,

21
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,280
like elbowing our teammates!

22
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:26,710
What are you thinking about?

23
00:03:28,930 --> 00:03:30,270
Those bandits.

24
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:33,030
Can't believe those farmers in the southwest

25
00:03:33,110 --> 00:03:34,440
were actually trained by the village chief.

26
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,030
Yeah.

27
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,870
They climbed the high-rise

28
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,430
with bare hands

29
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,360
and pulled it off every time!

30
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:42,310
It took us

31
00:03:42,310 --> 00:03:43,190
over a month of stakeout

32
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,870
to finally crack this case.

33
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:46,910
I'm speechless.

34
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,120
C'mon...

35
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,240
The case is over.

36
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:54,190
Take your time to chill out.

37
00:04:15,290 --> 00:04:16,070
Your lipstick color

38
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:17,390
matches your skin tone perfectly.

39
00:04:20,829 --> 00:04:21,630
I've never seen you before.

40
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:22,890
Are you a newcomer?

41
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:24,620
I joined just two days ago.

42
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,510
My name is Song Ying.

43
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,190
What's your name?

44
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,240
I'm Huang Ying

45
00:04:33,060 --> 00:04:33,720
We're both "Ying"!

46
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:34,810
What a coincidence.

47
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,040
Could you let me know if you need help in receiving guests?

48
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,159
Sure, no problem.

49
00:04:46,950 --> 00:04:47,630
Hurry up.

50
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,159
What are you doing?

51
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:50,450
The guests are waiting for me.

52
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,070
Those poor guys in your room

53
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,890
even ordered beers in half-dozens.

54
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:56,120
Why not join me for a feast tonight?

55
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,510
A guest sent the invitation.

56
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,190
Who's it?

57
00:04:58,510 --> 00:04:59,390
So generous.

58
00:04:59,909 --> 00:05:01,000
The guest you met

59
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:01,800
yesterday.

60
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:03,480
The one with long hair

61
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:04,600
and a mustache.

62
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,600
He's interested in you.

63
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:06,660
Be smart tonight.

64
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:07,870
Okay.

65
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:09,000
I'm heading back now.

66
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,600
I'll wait for you.

67
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:10,270
And be quick!

68
00:05:38,730 --> 00:05:41,190
Zhao! Zhao! Come here!

69
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:44,450
Block here...

70
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,440
Where did all this nasty water come from?

71
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,110
It stinks!

72
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:49,110
Can't stop it...

73
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,120
Too stinky...

74
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,190
Hurry...

75
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:56,630
Can't stop it at all...

76
00:05:56,630 --> 00:05:58,270
I can't fix the toilet either!

77
00:05:58,510 --> 00:05:59,390
-What a mess...
-Go...

78
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:00,510
Go there and get more tools.

79
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:01,310
I got it...

80
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,000
I got it...

81
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,160
The plunger didn't work?

82
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,520
No.

83
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:06,360
The bathroom is a complete mess.

84
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,130
How about this?

85
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,360
I'll ask the engineering department

86
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:09,200
to bring their tools

87
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:10,750
and go to 102 to check it out right away.

88
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,080
I told you not to dump the leftovers

89
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,170
into the toilet.

90
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,790
You didn't listen. Now look at this mess!

91
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:20,000
There's no way I poured this!

92
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,850
It's obviously not leftover food!

93
00:06:22,130 --> 00:06:22,750
Apparently, it's

94
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,160
the meat stuffing poured from upstairs.

95
00:06:25,790 --> 00:06:26,520
Meat stuffing?

96
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:34,810
There are always weirdos in this big world.

97
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,620
We've just had a few days of peace!

98
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:41,980
It's all hair.

99
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,159
Well,

100
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,510
no wonder it's clogged!

101
00:06:52,140 --> 00:06:53,750
The people upstairs are way too irresponsible!

102
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:00,000
Guys, what is that?

103
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,750
It's a finger!

104
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:08,510
Emergency call.

105
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,160
Some unknown body parts were found

106
00:07:10,190 --> 00:07:11,560
in Bishui Garden Residential Compound.

107
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:15,920
The things

108
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:16,840
that gushed out of the sewer

109
00:08:16,950 --> 00:08:18,120
include painted nails

110
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:19,070
and hair.

111
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,070
It's a criminal case.

112
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,320
We're leaving it to your department.

113
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:30,750
I'll go upstairs to pack up.

114
00:08:30,990 --> 00:08:32,299
You two wait for me behind the building.

115
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:33,789
No.

116
00:08:33,990 --> 00:08:34,559
It's too dangerous.

117
00:08:34,929 --> 00:08:36,210
It's more dangerous not to take anything.

118
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:48,390
Is that thing rotten?

119
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,720
And who else?

120
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:11,950
My mom and dad.

121
00:10:12,310 --> 00:10:13,360
Only the three of you?

122
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:17,080
Hello.

123
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:18,550
Hello...

124
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,360
Hi, sir.

125
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,080
Do you live in this building?

126
00:10:21,410 --> 00:10:22,140
We're from that building.

127
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:23,510
Building 3.

128
00:10:23,700 --> 00:10:24,580
Building 3?

129
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:28,730
Are you going on a long journey?

130
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:32,270
To the south for a vacation!

131
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,030
He's insane,

132
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:34,320
bringing such a big leather bag.

133
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,510
It's freezing cold here,

134
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:36,000
seriously.

135
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,600
It's so cold.

136
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:37,630
Let's go. They're waiting for us!

137
00:10:37,650 --> 00:10:38,510
Hurry up.

138
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:39,700
What happened?

139
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,930
S-So many people here...

140
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:05,960
Hello.

141
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:06,790
Please hold on.

142
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:09,390
Do you live here?

143
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:10,510
Yes.

144
00:11:11,150 --> 00:11:12,000
Where are you going?

145
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,910
I'm taking out the trash.

146
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:16,670
I'm a cop.

147
00:11:17,470 --> 00:11:19,090
Could you tell me which room you live in?

148
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:19,910
401.

149
00:11:22,930 --> 00:11:23,450
OK.

150
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,870
Do the upstairs and downstairs

151
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:27,910
share the same sewer?

152
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,350
I don't know.

153
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:31,550
Thank you.

154
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,200
Did anything go wrong?

155
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:33,790
Nope.

156
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,320
Come here!

157
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:12,080
Hey! Come here!

158
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:14,670
Give me a hand! C'mon!

159
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:17,960
Give me a hand.

160
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,720
Come on...

161
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:24,760
What is it?

162
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:25,750
The strong stench!

163
00:12:25,930 --> 00:12:26,480
What the heck is it?

164
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:53,240
I noticed something was off

165
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,150
when I reached the entrance.

166
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:55,550
So I turned around to wait

167
00:12:55,550 --> 00:12:56,200
for you at the back gate.

168
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:58,000
It means you've become quick-witted.

169
00:12:59,550 --> 00:13:00,590
I'm picking your brain while working.

170
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:01,870
Did you keep someone's brain?

171
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:04,150
He means

172
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,600
learning while working.

173
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,600
He didn't get anyone's brain.

174
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,320
You're so interesting, Hongyu.

175
00:13:09,210 --> 00:13:10,450
You talk too much every day.

176
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:10,870
Big bro,

177
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:11,720
did you bring all my things out?

178
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:12,980
Yeah, all the necessary stuff.

179
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,240
Including my cigarettes?

180
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:14,750
I just opened that pack.

181
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:17,360
What?

182
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:20,630
Cigarettes.

183
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:09,320
Come upstairs

184
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:10,030
to 402.

185
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:25,960
Do you think

186
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:29,590
the cop I ran into

187
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:31,970
will start suspecting me soon?

188
00:15:36,910 --> 00:15:37,960
No suspicion on the spot, of course.

189
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:39,940
But he'll surely find you suspicious later.

190
00:15:42,090 --> 00:15:42,850
Yeah...

191
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:21,380
Over all these years of work...

192
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,220
It's also the first time I've seen such a case.

193
00:16:25,690 --> 00:16:27,360
Do you think

194
00:16:29,450 --> 00:16:31,480
401 and 402

195
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,490
share the same sewer?

196
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:37,390
What sewer?

197
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:43,440
Hello.

198
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:44,960
Did you knock on the door just now?

199
00:16:44,980 --> 00:16:45,570
Yes, it was me.

200
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:46,790
I'm a cop.

201
00:16:47,290 --> 00:16:47,840
Well,

202
00:16:47,870 --> 00:16:49,120
can I go in and ask you a few questions?

203
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:50,750
Come in, please...

204
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:51,390
Come on in.

205
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:53,240
Hello, sir.

206
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,270
Madam.

207
00:16:55,570 --> 00:16:56,270
Have a seat.

208
00:16:56,270 --> 00:16:57,240
Don't bother, m-madam.

209
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:58,640
I just wanna know

210
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:00,360
if you've ever seen

211
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,390
your neighbor next door?

212
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,000
No.

213
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,359
Like, never?

214
00:17:04,510 --> 00:17:04,960
Never.

215
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:07,069
Then,

216
00:17:07,339 --> 00:17:08,750
have you heard the din

217
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:09,960
over the past few days?

218
00:17:11,450 --> 00:17:13,440
I can't hear things clearly.

219
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:17,670
Your son's still not back from taking out the trash?

220
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,030
I don't have a son.

221
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:20,460
I only have one daughter

222
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:21,960
who's doing business

223
00:17:22,339 --> 00:17:23,210
in Hailar.

224
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,110
A man in a red sweater with long hair,

225
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:30,110
heading out to dump the trash,

226
00:17:30,110 --> 00:17:31,440
is very likely the suspect.

227
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,240
Send someone to check all cars going out of the city.

228
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,160
Hello?

229
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:47,440
Okay.

230
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:48,750
Understood.

231
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:50,830
Chen!

232
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,480
They're closing off this highway

233
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:53,510
for ad hoc police checks.

234
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:57,740
Tell them to drive back.

235
00:17:57,830 --> 00:17:58,270
Got it.

236
00:17:58,830 --> 00:17:59,950
The police are doing ad hoc checks!

237
00:17:59,990 --> 00:18:00,510
Back off!

238
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:01,810
Back, back.

239
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,030
This road is closed!

240
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:05,160
The police are doing ad hoc checks!

241
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:07,070
Back off!

242
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:08,830
This road is closed off!

243
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:09,940
Go up there!

244
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:10,960
Ad hoc police checks.

245
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:24,320
What's wrong with you? How did you drive?

246
00:18:24,550 --> 00:18:25,920
You hit my car!

247
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,110
You crashed into me!

248
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:27,720
What?

249
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:28,350
Drive forward!

250
00:18:28,510 --> 00:18:29,030
He told me to back off!

251
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:29,960
You were supposed to drive forward!

252
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,350
Why should I drive forward?

253
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:32,460
That gesture means driving forward!

254
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:33,270
Can you drive properly?

255
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,510
How many years have you been driving?

256
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,750
Can you really drive?

257
00:18:35,790 --> 00:18:36,270
Are you blind?

258
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:36,720
Can you drive?

259
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,200
Can you...

260
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,030
Go foward now!

261
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:48,440
Only drive forward on the highway!

262
00:19:03,900 --> 00:19:04,860
What are you thinking about?

263
00:19:06,510 --> 00:19:07,230
Nothing.

264
00:19:07,650 --> 00:19:08,480
They're fighting.

265
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:10,510
Do or die.

266
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:26,790
Stop arguing.

267
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:28,440
Make way!

268
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:29,330
Don't get in the way!

269
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:31,790
Enough... Listen to me.

270
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:40,070
There's a traffic jam behind. You go first.

271
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:41,500
Let them go.

272
00:19:41,820 --> 00:19:43,140
Hu, let them go first.

273
00:19:43,210 --> 00:19:43,520
OK!

274
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:44,000
OK!

275
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:45,160
Get in the car...

276
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:46,430
Enough. Stop arguing.

277
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,400
Hurry! Get in the car...

278
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:49,350
Move the car.

279
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:50,200
Just make way.

280
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:50,830
Get in the car!

281
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,200
We didn't find any suspicious vehicles

282
00:20:02,530 --> 00:20:03,110
during our checks

283
00:20:03,110 --> 00:20:04,030
on the cars driving out of the city.

284
00:20:04,650 --> 00:20:05,680
After that, we started

285
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:06,510
a search in Bishui Garden

286
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:08,520
and found the rental information

287
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:09,200
about Room 402, Unit 1.

288
00:20:10,790 --> 00:20:11,510
What's the name of the person

289
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:12,200
who rented your house?

290
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:14,440
Li Jianfeng.

291
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:16,550
He rented my house for three months.

292
00:20:16,770 --> 00:20:18,010
1,500 yuan per month.

293
00:20:18,270 --> 00:20:20,030
T-The lease isn't due yet.

294
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,110
Show me the contract.

295
00:20:21,130 --> 00:20:21,930
There you are.

296
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:25,000
